{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2832fb11-1a20-4979-a4a3-a8a9e9300d79","content":"Use `#if` preprocessor directives with platform-specific compilation constants in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Place each platform implementation under its respective `Platforms/` folder (e.g., `Platforms/Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs`).\n- The constants `ANDROID`, `IOS`, and `WINDOWS` are defined automatically by the MAUI build targets — no manual setup needed.\n- This compiles only the relevant registration per target, so there's no runtime risk of referencing a missing platform type.\n- If you later add MacCatalyst, use `#elif MACCATALYST`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4a68ae22-f501-4836-99f2-ab682431d2db","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` interface in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not tied to any code in the current directory.","outputTokens":375,"requestId":"3C39:B0194:D7E43D:10CF154:6A012AF9"},"id":"8322bf48-a149-40ab-9ff0-c0558e59996c","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:05:19.447Z","parentId":"a7c72d95-340a-4c5e-bab6-00ae5e6e9cde"}
